legious challenge of lay misbehaviour and sin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity in literature. 0aChurch buildings in literature. 0aChurch historyyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 0aRight and left (Political science)zGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialismzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 4aMedieval Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aLollardy.  aMiddle English.  aarchitecture.  achurch.  alaity.  aperformance.  aprofane.  asacred space.  astained glass.1 aVarnam, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612181340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526121813423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526121813/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles